---
import SiteLayout from '../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';

const title = 'Privacy & Cookie Notice';
const description = 'How analytics, cookies, and personal data are handled on Puffs of Smoke.';
const lastUpdated = 'November 14, 2025';
---

<SiteLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <section class="py-12">
    <div class="container-page mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-10">
      <header class="space-y-3 text-center">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold tracking-[0.15em] text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">Transparency first</p>
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-semibold lg:text-5xl">{title}</h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-[var(--color-text-subtle)]">
          This page explains what limited information I collect when you visit, how cookies are used, and the choices you
          have while browsing jonkohlmeier.com.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
      </header>

      <article class="space-y-8 rounded-[2.5rem] border border-[var(--color-border-strong)] bg-[var(--color-surface)]/95 p-8 shadow-[var(--shadow-soft)]">
        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">What data is collected?</h2>
          <p>
            I use Google Analytics 4 (GA4) to understand aggregate traffic patterns—page views, referral sources, and
            approximate geography. GA4 masks IP addresses and does not reveal individual identities. Outside of GA4, the
            site only stores the preferences you explicitly choose (such as theme or consent choices) in your browser.
          </p>
          <p>
            If you contact me through the site or subscribe to updates, any details you submit are used solely to reply
            to you. They are not shared or sold.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Cookies & local storage</h2>
          <p>
            GA4 requires cookies to differentiate anonymous visits. Those cookies only load after you tap “Allow
            analytics” on the consent banner. You can decline at any time, and analytics code will stay disabled until
            you opt back in.
          </p>
          <p>
            The site also uses local storage keys for the appearance toggle (<code>theme</code>) and your consent choice
            (<code>analytics-consent</code>). These stay on your device and can be cleared by removing site data in your
            browser settings.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Your choices</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
            <li>
              Use the consent banner (or clear the <code>analytics-consent</code> entry) to change whether analytics run.
            </li>
            <li>
              Disable or remove cookies via your browser’s privacy controls—they take precedence over anything on this
              site.
            </li>
            <li>
              Reach out if you would like your prior correspondence removed or updated. You can always contact me at{' '}
              <a class="underline decoration-[var(--color-accent)] decoration-2 underline-offset-4" href="mailto:hello@jonkohlmeier.com">
                hello@jonkohlmeier.com
              </a>{' '}
              or through the <a class="underline decoration-[var(--color-accent)] decoration-2 underline-offset-4" href="/contact/">contact page</a>.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Questions?</h2>
          <p>
            Privacy is an ongoing practice. If you spot something unclear or want to request additional details, please
            send a note. I’ll respond personally and update this page whenever policies change.
          </p>
        </section>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
